@Node Description "Description"

  Description
  ===========

    This door is used to add adverts using external CLI programs to uploaded
    files.

    It uses a config file to decide what adder program to use depending on
    the uploaded file's extension.

@EndNode

@Node Installation "Installation"

  Installation
  ============

    The doors is stored as HBBS:Doors/System/Adverts/Adverts.HBBS

    This is included and enabled with a fresh installation of HydraBBS
    since V1.04.  Users of prior version should do this:

    Add the following lines to the appropriate "commands/system" file:

    Adverts_Type_1=HBBS
    Adverts_Door_1=HBBS:Doors/System/Adverts/Adverts.HBBS {N} {O}

    See HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Commands/System for an example

    It has an example config, which will have been installed as

    HBBS:Storage/Example_Configs/Doors/System/Adverts/Adverts.CFG

    Please edit this config file accordingly and save it as

    HBBS:Doors/System/Adverts/Adverts.CFG


    You will need to find suitable addvert adder/stripper programs,
    these are available from Aminet.  Mapus V1.16 is included
    and stored in HBBS:System/Amiga/CLI for DMS files. LHA, ZIP and
    LZX work fine too (for adding adverts, but not for stipping them)

    Example screens are included, but are NOT installed as part of the
    upgrade procedure, see HBBS:Storage/Example_Screens/Special.

    Adverts are normally just plain text files, try and keep your adverts
    as small as possible to avoid bloating archive file sizes.

    Make a directory called HBBS:Storage/Adverts and store your adverts
    in there, this will keep them with your HBBS setup.

@EndNode

