@Node ConfigFiles "ConfigFiles"

  Config Files
  ============

    This program uses "Progdir:Adverts.CFG", i.e:

    HBBS:Doors/System/Adverts/Adverts.CFG

  Options
  =======

  All options must be specified for each type of file.

  Where <ext> is the extension of a file, e.g. for "test.lha" it would be "LHA"

    FileTypeDesc_<ext>=<String>    @{" More... " link CFG_FileTypeDesc}
    AdderCMD_<ext>=<String>        @{" More... " link CFG_AdderCMD}
    AdderParams_<ext>=<String>     @{" More... " link CFG_AdderParams}
    ShowOutput_<ext>=<Boolean>     @{" More... " link CFG_ShowOutput}

  Example
  =======

  FileTypeDesc_LHA=LHA Archive
  AdderCMD_LHA=LHA
  AdderParams_LHA=a -Qa -M -N -x0 @F@ HBBS:Storage/Adverts/Named/#?
  ShowOutput_LHA=NO

  Say you were on node 3 an uploaded TEST.LHA using the above settings, the
  actual command that would be executed would be:

  LHA a -Qa -M -N TEST.LHA HBBS:Storage/Adverts/Named/#?

  Add all the files in HBBS:Storage/Adverts/Named would be added to the
  archive but the path would be stripped (using -x0)

@EndNode

@Node CFG_FileTypeDesc "FileTypeDesc"

  FileTypeDesc_<ext>=<String>

    E.G.

    FileTypeDesc_LHA=LHA Archive

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This is a string that is displayed to the users, telling them what
    kind of file is being checked.

@EndNode

@Node CFG_AdderCMD "AdderCMD"

  AdderCMD_<ext>=<String>

    E.G.

    AdderCMD_LHA=LHA

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This option specifies the actuall amigados program to run.

    The current directory is set to the node's playpen directory before the
    command is run.

    The command must be in the path, otherwise you must specify a full path
    and file name, e.g. AdderCMD_LHA=SYS:Utilities/Archivers/LHA

    The command you use must be able to have all of it's output re-directed
    to a file using standard redirection.  e.g. For LHA you might try
    "LHA >ram:test t my_file.lha" to see if it works.

@EndNode

@Node CFG_AdderParams "AdderParams"

  AdderParams_<ext>=<String>

    E.G.

    AdderParams_LHA=t -Qa -M -N -x0 @F@ HBBS:Storage/Adverts/Named/#?

    No Default, Must Be Set!

    This option specifies the paramaters to be passed to the adder,
    It should include things like the filename and any required options.

    If the adder has switches to make the output as small as possible
    then use them.  Also, if the adder has options to use simple IO
    and/or no ANSI then use those options too. (if you want)

    It is a good idea to have the adder program NOT store the path names for
    the adverts.

    The adder command string is checked for @ codes, the following
    are recognised:

    @F@ is replaced with the filename of the uploaded file
    @N@ is replaced with just the filename of the uploaded file
    @E@ is replaced with the filename's extension
    @P@ is replaced with the path of the filename (but not including the name
    itself)

    So, say you were on node 3 and uploaded TEST.LHA the following @ codes
    above would give you the following results (without the quotes)

    @F@ "TEST.LHA"
    @N@ "TEST"
    @E@ "LHA"
    @P@ "HBBS:Nodes/Node3/Playpen/"

@EndNode

@Node CFG_ShowOutput "ShowOutput"

  ShowOutput_<ext>=<Boolean>

    E.G.

    ShowOutput_LHA=YES

    When this is set to TRUE the output from the adder command will be
    displayed to the user.

@EndNode

